description:
&lt;p&gt;At South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust, we are passionate about providing the best possible care and outcomes for our Children, Young People and Families across Warwickshire. This is a stimulating and challenging role which will enable you to care for children with complex healthcare needs within their home, school environment and a variety of other settings. We are seeking highly skilled, resourceful, adaptable, enthusiastic Clinical Support Workers who are motivated to really make a difference to the lives of the Children and Young People and Families we care for. You must be forward thinking, have excellent interpersonal and organisational skills. You will need to be calm in a crisis, quick to learn and happy to work rotational shift patterns. You must be prepared to undertake our comprehensive evidence based Coventry and Warwickshire interactive e-competency training and the SWFT Care Certificate. You will be supported by qualified nurses within the team providing high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Children’s Nursing Team works in close collaboration with primary, secondary, tertiary care in health, education, social care and with other multi-disciplinary partners, to ensure excellent evidence based care is delivered to Children, Young People and their Families with complex healthcare needs in a variety of settings, avoiding unnecessary hospital admissions and ensuring seamless care is delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It is recommended that you contact us for an informal chat or visit. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please provide evidence in your application form of your qualifications and experience as detailed in the Person Specification&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It is recommended that you contact us for an informal chat or visit. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
